603
00:28:30,640 --> 00:28:32,200
I think

604
00:28:32,200 --> 00:28:34,760
she may have written

605
00:28:34,760 --> 00:28:35,720
an acrostic poetry by accident.

606
00:28:38,640 --> 00:28:39,760
Alright. It’s definitely a prank.

607
00:28:40,560 --> 00:28:42,000
But Jiang Haoyue was worse.

608
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:44,560
He’s so annoying.

609
00:28:44,560 --> 00:28:46,320
He’s extremely treacherous.

610
00:28:46,760 --> 00:28:48,200
He replaced your speech.

611
00:28:48,560 --> 00:28:50,080
This act is very

612
00:28:52,280 --> 00:28:53,640
irritating

613
00:28:53,640 --> 00:28:54,320
and shameless.

614
00:28:57,400 --> 00:28:58,400
I’ll get even with him for sure.

615
00:29:14,280 --> 00:29:15,400
Jiang.

616
00:29:15,400 --> 00:29:16,120
Uncle Lu.

617
00:29:17,960 --> 00:29:19,000
Throwing the trash?

618
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:20,040
Yeah, I am.

619
00:29:20,960 --> 00:29:21,760
I need to throw them first.

620
00:29:25,240 --> 00:29:25,960
Jiang.

621
00:29:29,640 --> 00:29:30,400
Have you had dinner?

622
00:29:39,160 --> 00:29:40,200
Here. Jiang.

623
00:29:49,480 --> 00:29:50,440
Well. Enjoy your food.

624
00:29:50,440 --> 00:29:51,600
Thank you, Sir.

625
00:29:51,600 --> 00:29:52,520
No problem.

626
00:29:54,240 --> 00:29:55,120
Come on. Jiang.

627
00:29:55,120 --> 00:29:55,880
Eat now.

628
00:30:04,200 --> 00:30:04,720
Uncle Lu.

629
00:30:06,440 --> 00:30:09,000
Did you pay for my artificial leg?

630
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:09,640
Of course not.

631
00:30:10,880 --> 00:30:12,160
What are you thinking about?

632
00:30:12,880 --> 00:30:16,600
Jiang, you should thank
your father for it.

633
00:30:16,600 --> 00:30:17,760
Here comes your food.

634
00:30:17,760 --> 00:30:18,440
Thanks.

635
00:30:19,040 --> 00:30:19,680
My father?

636
00:30:21,760 --> 00:30:23,920
Your father cares about you a lot.

637
00:30:26,720 --> 00:30:28,400
You are

638
00:30:28,400 --> 00:30:29,560
a great kid.

639
00:30:30,800 --> 00:30:32,720
But I have to say sometimes

640
00:30:32,720 --> 00:30:33,840
you’re too suspicious.

641
00:30:34,920 --> 00:30:37,000
When have I ever lied to you?

642
00:30:39,160 --> 00:30:39,720
I’m sorry.

643
00:30:43,240 --> 00:30:44,520
That’s not what I mean.

644
00:30:45,200 --> 00:30:46,880
No, Uncle Lu.

645
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:49,880
I shouldn’t have been mad at you

646
00:30:49,880 --> 00:30:51,120
